$begin pow_reverse$$
$spell
    Taylor
$$

$section Exponential Function Reverse Mode Theory$$

We use the reverse theory
$cref%standard math function
    %ReverseTheory
    %Standard Math Functions
%$$
definition for the functions $latex H$$ and $latex G$$.
The zero order forward mode formula for the
$cref/power/pow_forward/$$ function is
$latex \[
    z^{(0)}  =  F ( x^{(0)} )
\] $$
All the equations below apply to the case where $latex j > 0$$
where the equation for $latex z^{(j)}$$ is
$latex \[
z^{(j)}
=
\left. \left(
	y z^{(0)} x^{(j)}
	+
	\frac{y-1}{j} \sum_{k=1}^{j-1} k z^{(k)}  x^{(j-k)}
\right) \right/ x^{(0)}
\] $$

$head x^j$$
$latex \[
\begin{array}{rcl}
\D{H}{ x^{(j)} }
& = & \D{G}{ x^{(j)} }  + \D{G}{ z^{(j)} } \D{ z^{(j)} }{ x^{(j)} }
\\
\D{ z^{(j)} }{ x^{(j)} } & = & y z^{(0)} / x^{(0)}
\end{array}
\] $$

$head x^k$$
For $latex k = 1 , \ldots , j-1$$
$latex \[
\begin{array}{rcl}
\D{H}{ x^{(k)} }
& = & \D{G}{ x^{(k)} }  + \D{G}{ z^{(j)} } \D{ z^{(j)} }{ x^{(k)} }
\\
\D{ z^{(j)} }{ x^{(k)} } & = &  \frac{y-1}{j} (j-k) z^{(j-k)} / x^{(0)}
\end{array}
\] $$

$head z^k$$
For $latex k = 1 , \ldots , j-1$$
$latex \[
\begin{array}{rcl}
\D{H}{ z^{(k)} }
& = & \D{G}{ z^{(k)} }  + \D{G}{ z^{(j)} } \D{ z^{(j)} }{ z^{(k)} }
\\
\D{ z^{(j)} }{ z^{(k)} } & = &  \frac{y-1}{j} k x^{(j-k)} / x^{(0)}
\end{array}
\] $$

$head x^0$$
$latex \[
\begin{array}{rcl}
\D{H}{ x^{(0)} }
& = & \D{G}{ x^{(0)} }  + \D{G}{ z^{(j)} } \D{ z^{(j)} }{ x^{(0)} }
\\
\D{ z^{(j)} }{ x^{(0)} }
& = &
 - \left. \left(
	y z^{(0)} x^{(j)}
	+
	\frac{y-1}{j} \sum_{k=1}^{j-1} k z^{(k)}  x^{(j-k)}
\right) \right/ ( x^{(0)} x^{(0)} )
\end{array}
\] $$

$end
